The National Union of Teachers (NUT) in Adamawa State has called on all its affiliate unions, the Association of Nigerian Conference of Principals of Secondary Schools, ANCOPSS and Association of Primary School Head Teachers of Nigeria, AOPSHTON and all teachers to strictly adhere to the circular of the state government on schools closure. In a statement issued by NUT the state Chairman, Comrade Rodney Nathan said the circular for closure of schools was a preventative measure against the Coronavirus pandemic bedeviling the country. Nathan also noted that the circular by the Ministry of Education was timely in view of the spread of the disease across the globe, describing it as worrisome. He called on parents to take good care of their wards from contacting the disease while the schools closure lasted.